ActCustoms Tariff
SubjectCPFTA Rules of Origin Regulations
PrecisCanada-Peru Free Trade Agreement Rules of Origin Regulations (CPFTA) implement, in Canada, the rules of origin negotiated by Canada and Peru, which will be used to determine when goods have undergone sufficient production to qualify for preferential tariff treatment under the CPFTA. Preferential tariff treatment under the CPFTA, which reflects the actual reduction in specific rates of duty, has been implemented in the Customs Tariff through Bill C-24.
